Timsort is an efficient sorting algorithm that can be used to sort lists or arrays in ascending or descending order. In Lean 4, the Timsort algorithm can be implemented as follows:

def timsort(arr):
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        min_idx = i
        for j in range(i + 1, len(arr)):
            if arr[min_idx] > arr[j]:
                min_idx = j

        arr[i] = arr[min_idx]

    return arr

This function takes in an array or list and returns the sorted version of the input. The algorithm works by comparing two adjacent elements and swapping them if the first element is greater than the second. This process is repeated until the entire list is sorted.
